10/07/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- An overwhelming majority of 84.6 per cent of Greeks view the attacks against London as criminal acts, while only 8 per cent view them as acts of resistance against big powers, according to a poll by the Kappa research agency, published in the newspaper To Vima Saturday (9 July). Only 33 per cent of respondents believe that the attack will have negative consequences for Greece. (ERA - 09/07/05) 
